The paper discusses the distribution of citations for academic articles in different subject categories, which is a topic relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. However, the focus on Scopus categories suggests a stronger connection to information retrieval (cs.IR), digital libraries (cs.DL), social networks (cs.SI), cryptography (cs.CY), and computer vision (cs.CR).
